ve space is allotted for offices and academic departments  A drive area is created for instructional use  allowing write access to faculty and read access by students  All users with network accounts have personal mailboxes  Departmental Directory Quota All Departments   500MB Email Cadets   Warning 55MB Prohibit Send 60MB Prohibit Send and Receive 65MB Faculty and Staff   Warning 90MB Prohibit Send 95MB Prohibit Send and Receive 100MB   Personal Directory Cadets 100MB Faculty and Staff 200MB   VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI  RESOURCES   Title IX  Health   Safety   IT   Site Index Parents   Families   Cadets   Non discrimination Statement   Privacy   THE VMI PHILOSOPHY The VMI experience is framed by relevant education within a military environment  It s an education that develops character  fosters a lifelong appreciation of physical fitness engenders a sense of responsibility to others  and cultivates the ability to master adversity  VIRGINIA MILITARY INSTITUTE Lexington  Virginia 24450 General Information   540  464 7230  Admissions  admissions vmi edu 